				<td colspan="2"><span>A moderate is not necessarily middle of the road.  But instead someone who realizes that issues are not black and white and therefore want to get to know the whole issue as best they can to make a good decision.  Being to the far left or right in thinking takes away the grey but makes everything black and white and removes the middle ground, so there is nowhere you can meet inbetween.
<br />

<br />
I am a moderate Democratic-Republican.  I see the world in shades of grey with a bit of black and white in there, too.  And I have definate stances on many issues, I'm not wishy washy at all.  Prove my view is wrong, and I mean PROVE, not just beat me over the head with dogma and such, and I will consider changing my view.  There are some views I will not change.  But those are another discussion all together.</span></td>
