				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Conservatism and Liberalism...<a name="44160"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 4 04 11:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Our legislature was designed to appease those who wanted each state to have equal represenation, and those who wanted to be represented on a population per capita basis.
<br />

<br />
In other words, the framers had to please Rhode Island AND Virginia when forming this branch of government.
<br />

<br />
Our legislature is loosely based off of the Brits, with the House of Lords and Commons being the Senate and House of Represenatatives respectively.
<br />

<br />
Senators serve longer terms.  The intent (IMO) is that their longer terms allow them to distance themselves from state matters and consider the overall picture when making laws.
<br />

<br />
The House is shorter term, and usually attempts to serve the best interests of the folks who elected them.
<br />

<br />
